        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Creating a Zend_Form with a config\/array doesn't support setting validator's message templates. It would be simple to add this \nwith a setValidatorMessages() method to Zend_Form_Element. The setOptions will then transform a array\/config's 'validatorMessages' key and call the method.\n\nOr is this the wrong way to go? Perhaps it's more appropriate to do any relevant validator setMessage calls from a sub-classed form class? It seems to be write more classes vs grow the config. Hmm. Now I'm beginning to wish I hadn't raised the issue.\n"
        },
